      "searchTerms": "phase 3a character forge handbook  {\"title\":\"phase 3a character forge\",\"type\":\"handbook\",\"category\":\"gameplay architecture\",\"tags\":[\"gameplay\",\"character-forge\",\"phase-3a\"],\"visibility\":\"public\"} # phase 3a character forge\n\n## overview\ncharacter forge replaces the old creator label and becomes the guided character build foundation for asteria.\n\n## forge flow\n1. race\n2. class\n3. appearance\n4. origin\n5. characteristics\n6. skills\n7. equipment\n8. review\n\n## rules\nclass talents are displayed from class progression data and are not freely selected during the forge flow.\n\nprofession slots start as \"no profession learned\" and remain campaign-earned.\n\nstarting skill selection requires exactly 4 skills from the skill compendium.\n\n## compatibility\nthe older internal create-character route remains as a compatibility alias so existing dashboard buttons, saves, and account routes open character forge instead of breaking."
